                        <docTitle>MEMORANDUM OF OBJECTS AND REASONS</docTitle>
                    </p>
                </preface>
                <mainBody>
                    <container id="ctn1" name="objects">
                        <p>
                            The objective of this Bill is to amend the Constitution to facilitate
                            the re-publication and re-introduction of the draft Constitution
                            into the National Assembly for re-consideration. This will enable
                            the National Assembly address the contentious issues which have
                            polarised the country following the publication of the proposed
                            Constitution by the Attorney-General. The re-publication of the
                            Bill contemplated in the Bill would be necessitated if the
                            National Assembly votes to have the draft Constitution amended
                            to resolve the contentious issues which have arisen following the
                            publication of the proposed Constitution. Similarly, this Bill
                            seeks to lower the threshold required to approve the draft
                            Constitution by the National Assembly, from sixty-five per cent
                            of the members, to a majority of the members.
                            The enactment of this Bill shall entail additional
                            expenditure of public funds to be provided for through the
                            estimates.
                        </p>
                    </container>
                </mainBody>
                <conclusions>
